51 // Constructor/Destrurctor
52 StateMachineOut::StateMachineOut(ros::NodeHandle *nh) : nh(nh)
53 {
54  // Create ServiceClient
55  tclient = new Tapi::ServiceClient(nh, "StateMachine Output");
56  client = tclient->AddFeature<tapi_lib::GetStateMachine>("Get StateMachine States");
57 
58  // Create the subscriber to get the current state
59  tsub = new Tapi::Subscriber(nh, "StateMachine Output");
60  tsub->AddFeature(SubscribeOptionsForTapi(std_msgs::String, 10, &StateMachineOut::current), "Get Current State");
61 }
62 
63 StateMachineOut::~StateMachineOut()
64 {
65  delete tsub;
66  delete tclient;
67 }

71 void StateMachineOut::current(const std_msgs::String::ConstPtr &msg)
72 {
73  // Check whether the service is connected, then fetch the data about the states
74  if (!*client)
75  return;
76  tapi_lib::GetStateMachine getter;
77  getter.request.Get = true;
78  if ((*client)->call(getter))
79  {
80  // Store the states in a map
81  map<string, tapi_lib::State> states;
82  for (auto it = getter.response.States.begin(); it != getter.response.States.end(); ++it)
83  {
84  tapi_lib::State temp;
85  temp.ID = it->ID;
86  temp.Name = it->Name;
87  temp.Transitions = it->Transitions;
88  states.emplace(temp.ID, temp);
89  }
90 
91  // See if the current state is in the map
92  if (states.count(msg->data) > 0)
93  {
94  // Print information about the current state and its transitions on the console
95  tapi_lib::State temp;
96  temp = states.at(msg->data);
97  string name, id, transitions = "";
98  name = temp.Name;
99  id = temp.ID;
100  for (auto it = temp.Transitions.begin(); it != temp.Transitions.end(); ++it)
101  {
102  if (states.count(it->ToID) > 0)
103  {
104  string toName = states.at(it->ToID).Name;
105  transitions += ", can switch to state: " + toName + ", when: " + it->Condition;
106  }
107  else
108  ROS_ERROR("Wrong transition");
109  }
110  ROS_INFO("In state %s, id %s%s", name.c_str(), id.c_str(), transitions.c_str());
111  }
112  else
113  ROS_ERROR("Wrong state");
114  }
115 }
116 }
